<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Collingwood </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
        <p class="par-lg">Collingwood real estate was first established in 1959 after the area itself came under Calgary in 1910. The neighborhood is represented by the Ward 7 Councilor at the Calgary City Council.</p>
        <p class="par-xl">With the University of Calgary located at a walking distance, a major chunk of the residents in the community of Collingwood comprise of students and growing families.</p>
        <p class="par-lg">The average real estate pricing falls somewhere along the lines of $1 million, with some of the finest residential units being listed at $3.5 million or higher. With a major chunk of the Collingwood homes of sale comprising of single family homes, apartments and condominiums, nearly 25.9% of the housing options are available for rent.</p>
        </div>
